				<h2 class="title icon icon0">
					Weird Issue with Window Frame in Unity Mode
				</h2>
				

						
							
							
							
						
						
				<div class="content ">
					<div id="post_message_1739658">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							<a href="http://i.imgur.com/afOBm.png" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">http://i.imgur.com/afOBm.png</a>  So, when I use Unity Mode (in VMWare) (Or Seamless Mode in Virtual Box) the edges of the windows from the guest OS are are showing the desktop wallpaper on the edges of the windows.  Also, sometimes when resizing them the window will resize downwards, instead of increasing vertically like I was intending it to.  The main thing though is the weird drawing of the window frame edges.  This started happening when I upgraded to Ubuntu 12.04 and it is driving me crazy, so it may have something to do with the Unity Window Manager that the distro changed to.  That's just a guess though.  Thoughts?
						</blockquote>
					</div>

					
				</div>
			</div>
			
